{
  "stem": "19807.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We knew that we'd be in a kibbutz, we knew that we'd work in the farms, we'd be-- and we'd be studying in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So in the train, the-- the mood was not a mood of depression.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a mood of jubilation, but it was also a mood of-- of gratitude, saying, hey, again, to reiterate that, this train could have been going in a different direction.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Whoa.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was beautiful.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] --we arrived there, it was in the winter.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they received us there with open arms.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were 32, 34 children and young lads full of enthusiasm, full of life.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Most of us spoke Hebrew because we went to Hebrew school and those did not very quickly learned.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So in a way, I have a little bit of resentment that I did not study in a French college just like the rest of my cousins, but in the way I feel also grateful that-- that-- that-- that Zionism and that Jewishness was embedded so deep into me from day one.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were wonderful there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They called us the Bulgarians.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we used to dance the Horah all kinds of nights.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We worked a half a day and half a day we studied.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We had a wonderful teacher, a wonderful teacher.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "His name-- just he passed away.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I visited him two years ago.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We had a reunion, 50-year reunion, two years ago in Geva.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And also last month we had the 50th reunion of the kibbutz that we founded.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Now, we had two years in Geva.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "After that, we got together with several other groups, children primarily from Bulgaria, and those three groups, we formed a kibbutz in the desert.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
